WEBVTT

00:00:01.370 --> 00:00:04.540
If we return to the beta world line...

00:00:04.540 --> 00:00:06.450
...Makise Kurisu...

00:00:07.040 --> 00:00:08.410
...will die.

00:00:09.040 --> 00:00:12.830
-I'm gonna run the hack now.
-Wait!

00:00:12.830 --> 00:00:14.830
The hacking...

00:00:16.750 --> 00:00:18.290
...is canceled.

00:00:32.160 --> 00:00:37.370
For you, billions and billions of heartbeats

00:00:37.370 --> 00:00:44.040
are nothing at all; just the blink of an eye

00:00:44.040 --> 00:00:49.250
Although I'm trapped by
the past and lament the future

00:00:49.250 --> 00:00:55.160
inevitability won't allow for
even a speck of a miscalculation

00:00:55.160 --> 00:01:01.290
Our dreams and futures that
form and expand into "infinity"

00:01:01.290 --> 00:01:07.160
allow us the right to be vain,

00:01:07.160 --> 00:01:13.370
while the two hands
point out what is "finite"

00:01:13.370 --> 00:01:17.950
All of which leads to a cruel
contract and choice to make

00:01:17.950 --> 00:01:20.200
Hacking to the Gate

00:01:20.200 --> 00:01:27.120
So, now, with each passing
second, I'll cross world lines

00:01:27.120 --> 00:01:32.040
to protect that smile on your face

00:01:32.040 --> 00:01:39.040
Then, once again, into a
time loop without sadness

00:01:39.040 --> 00:01:45.750
I will be swallowed up as a lone observer

00:01:57.750 --> 00:01:58.660
Where's Okabe?

00:01:58.660 --> 00:02:01.830
Unknown! I've been busy!

00:02:01.830 --> 00:02:04.620
-Well, good luck to you, Mayushii!
-And to you, Daru-kun!

00:02:04.620 --> 00:02:06.370
Aye!

00:02:07.370 --> 00:02:10.290
-Is today the last day of Comima?
-Yeah.

00:02:10.290 --> 00:02:13.910
Do you want to come too?
There'll be lots of girls doing cute cosplays!

00:02:13.910 --> 00:02:17.330
I-I'm not interested in that sort of thing...

00:02:19.410 --> 00:02:21.290
I wonder what Okarin's up to.

00:02:21.290 --> 00:02:25.080
Beats me. He called off
the hack and then just left...

00:02:25.080 --> 00:02:27.330
Who knows what he's thinking...

00:02:31.910 --> 00:02:35.580
It's supposed to get up to 35º Celsius today!

00:02:35.580 --> 00:02:40.540
It's important to keep
hydrated or you'll get heat stroke!

00:02:40.540 --> 00:02:43.120
Aren't you going to Comima today?

00:02:43.120 --> 00:02:45.500
Yeah. I'm just about to leave.

00:02:45.500 --> 00:02:47.660
I see. Be careful.

00:02:47.660 --> 00:02:49.290
Right!

00:02:53.620 --> 00:02:55.750
The sun's really strong today.

00:02:55.750 --> 00:02:58.330
See you later! Too-too-roo!

00:02:59.040 --> 00:03:01.120
Mayuri...!

00:03:06.700 --> 00:03:09.000
August 17th...

00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:14.580
Each D-mail I've undone has
pushed Mayuri's death one day back.

00:03:14.580 --> 00:03:17.450
It started out on the 13th

00:03:17.450 --> 00:03:20.450
and moved to the 14th when
Suzuha's message was undone.

00:03:20.450 --> 00:03:23.120
Faris... Rukako... Moeka...

00:03:23.120 --> 00:03:26.790
If each one has delayed it by a day,

00:03:26.790 --> 00:03:31.080
then Mayuri will die on
the 17th on this world line.

00:03:31.080 --> 00:03:33.330
Today, just before 8:00 pm.

00:03:33.330 --> 00:03:35.080
That's the deadline...

00:03:35.080 --> 00:03:36.700
Okarin!

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:40.790
Find what you were looking for?

00:03:40.790 --> 00:03:44.410
Yeah! They were almost sold out, too!

00:03:44.410 --> 00:03:46.370
I even snagged some for Daru-kun!

00:03:46.370 --> 00:03:50.290
Oh, I also saw a book about
robot anime I bet you'd like!

00:03:50.290 --> 00:03:52.330
Want to see?

00:03:52.330 --> 00:03:54.250
No, that's okay.

00:03:54.250 --> 00:03:56.790
Why not? You're here and all...

00:03:56.790 --> 00:03:59.620
I just... have some things on my mind.

00:03:59.620 --> 00:04:01.120
Oh.

00:04:01.120 --> 00:04:04.250
If there's anywhere you
wanna see, just let me know!

00:04:04.250 --> 00:04:05.870
Yeah.

00:04:07.370 --> 00:04:08.660
Are you okay?

00:04:08.660 --> 00:04:10.410
Do you want to leave?

00:04:10.410 --> 00:04:13.040
D-Don't be silly!

00:04:13.040 --> 00:04:14.580
I just meant I'm concerned

00:04:14.580 --> 00:04:17.750
about the Organization
assassins lurking at this venue.

00:04:17.750 --> 00:04:20.540
We must outfox them somehow.

00:04:20.540 --> 00:04:23.120
They might spot us if we aren't careful.

00:04:23.120 --> 00:04:25.950
We will proceed as planned until evening falls.

00:04:25.950 --> 00:04:29.290
I don't think there's anyone that bad here.

00:04:29.290 --> 00:04:30.870
I'm going scouting.

00:04:30.870 --> 00:04:33.910
Reconvene here at 1500 hours. Understood?

00:04:33.910 --> 00:04:35.540
Okay!

00:04:36.450 --> 00:04:40.580
Okarin! They're selling drinks and
stuff over there, just so you know!

00:04:40.580 --> 00:04:42.250
Five hours left...

00:04:42.250 --> 00:04:43.580
Don't give up.

00:04:43.580 --> 00:04:45.870
You have to find it before then...

00:04:45.870 --> 00:04:50.450
A way for Mayuri to survive
without changing world lines.

00:04:51.790 --> 00:04:53.750
"Daru"
"Assistant"

00:04:56.580 --> 00:05:00.040
Huh?! Why do I have to help Hashida--?!

00:05:00.040 --> 00:05:02.290
A notebook listing all the clubs there?

00:05:02.290 --> 00:05:04.290
I don't see anything like that.

00:05:04.290 --> 00:05:05.290
The bookshelf?

00:05:05.290 --> 00:05:06.370
The second shelf has--

00:05:06.370 --> 00:05:08.700
Huh? Stay away from the second shelf?

00:05:08.700 --> 00:05:10.330
Oh...

00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:12.700
"Comima Club List"

00:05:12.870 --> 00:05:15.040
I'm seriously going to sue.

00:05:17.580 --> 00:05:19.660
-What?
-It's me.

00:05:19.660 --> 00:05:22.410
What's going on with the hacking?

00:05:22.410 --> 00:05:26.830
You called it off, so it's been
at a standstill for three days now.

00:05:26.830 --> 00:05:28.540
It's time you start explaining.

00:05:28.540 --> 00:05:30.580
What exactly happened?

00:05:30.580 --> 00:05:32.910
Mayuri... dies today.

00:05:32.910 --> 00:05:35.450
You already told me.

00:05:35.450 --> 00:05:37.580
That's why we're doing
the hacking, remember?

00:05:37.580 --> 00:05:40.660
-Once we delete the first D-mail you--
-No!

00:05:40.660 --> 00:05:42.580
No hacking.

00:05:42.580 --> 00:05:46.620
I need to come up with a way
to save Mayuri without hacking.

00:05:46.620 --> 00:05:48.250
Why?

00:05:49.540 --> 00:05:52.660
Because something new has come up.

00:05:52.660 --> 00:05:54.700
Like what?

00:05:54.700 --> 00:05:57.580
I can't explain right now.

00:05:57.580 --> 00:06:00.830
There has to be a way. Some other way...

00:06:00.830 --> 00:06:02.410
What do you mean?

00:06:02.410 --> 00:06:04.620
Please!

00:06:04.620 --> 00:06:06.290
Explain to me.

00:06:06.290 --> 00:06:11.830
I can't help you fix things
if you leave me in the dark.

00:06:14.870 --> 00:06:18.750
It's soon, right? This is no time
to hide things from me, Okabe!

00:06:28.910 --> 00:06:31.290
We're finally back!

00:06:31.290 --> 00:06:34.040
Say, want to stop by the lab, Okarin?

00:06:34.040 --> 00:06:37.410
Mayushii was thinking
of getting something to eat!

00:06:40.120 --> 00:06:42.910
Are you all tired out, Okarin?

00:06:42.910 --> 00:06:44.200
No...

00:06:45.660 --> 00:06:47.660
It's almost time...

00:06:47.660 --> 00:06:50.870
It's almost time for Mayuri to die again...

00:06:50.870 --> 00:06:51.950
Should we run?

00:06:51.950 --> 00:06:55.540
No, it'll still end like always...

00:06:55.540 --> 00:06:56.910
Okarin?

00:06:56.910 --> 00:06:58.330
Let's go.

00:07:08.120 --> 00:07:09.500
Say, Okarin.

00:07:09.500 --> 00:07:12.080
Why did you come with me today?

00:07:12.080 --> 00:07:15.410
You hardly looked around at anything.

00:07:15.410 --> 00:07:20.160
I could've shown you around more if
there was anything you wanted to see!

00:07:20.160 --> 00:07:24.580
Mayushii usually doesn't
know more than you, you know?

00:07:27.580 --> 00:07:29.450
Okarin...

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:38.040
Thanks for today!

00:07:38.040 --> 00:07:40.500
This was our first time
going to Comima together!

00:07:40.500 --> 00:07:43.540
Mayushii was glad!

00:07:43.540 --> 00:07:46.250
Mayuri...

00:07:46.250 --> 00:07:51.330
I had hoped to see Rukako acting
embarrassed in a cosplay outfit!

00:07:51.330 --> 00:07:53.000
It's a shame he didn't come!

00:07:53.000 --> 00:07:56.700
Yeah! I'm sure he would've been really popular!

00:07:56.700 --> 00:07:58.000
Definitely!

00:07:58.000 --> 00:08:01.830
Then his pictures would get
posted on blogs everywhere

00:08:01.830 --> 00:08:05.040
and he'd become a worldwide superstar!

00:08:05.040 --> 00:08:11.200
And then Mayushii would see
that and think, "He's come so far!"

00:08:11.200 --> 00:08:13.500
That almost sounds possible.

00:08:13.500 --> 00:08:16.790
I think I'd love it even more
if you cosplay next, Okarin!

00:08:16.790 --> 00:08:18.370
I'll think about it.

00:08:18.370 --> 00:08:19.450
Really?

00:08:19.450 --> 00:08:22.950
But only if you cosplay too, Mayuri.

00:08:22.950 --> 00:08:23.790
Huh?

00:08:23.790 --> 00:08:27.580
I know, let's invite Rukako and Christina.

00:08:27.580 --> 00:08:31.500
And then you can
convince them to cosplay too.

00:08:31.500 --> 00:08:37.040
Only then will I, the mad
scientist Hououin Kyouma,

00:08:37.040 --> 00:08:39.500
descend upon Comima as its star attraction!

00:08:39.500 --> 00:08:42.450
Oh, we have a tough road ahead of us!

00:08:42.450 --> 00:08:44.870
But Kurisu-chan was interested!

00:08:44.870 --> 00:08:48.250
Mayushii will try hard to convince
them before the next Comima!

00:08:48.250 --> 00:08:49.750
The next--

00:08:54.910 --> 00:08:56.410
Huh?

00:08:56.410 --> 00:08:59.660
Mayushii's watch has stopped...

00:08:59.660 --> 00:09:02.540
That's strange. I wound it up--

00:09:03.290 --> 00:09:05.000
Okarin?!

00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:06.870
No! No more!

00:09:06.870 --> 00:09:09.750
I've come so far! Why does it still...?!

00:09:09.750 --> 00:09:10.790
Okarin?!

00:09:10.790 --> 00:09:13.450
Just stay right here!

00:09:13.450 --> 00:09:16.120
Okarin!

00:09:16.120 --> 00:09:19.000
I will change it!

00:09:19.000 --> 00:09:21.410
I'll change fate myself!

00:09:21.410 --> 00:09:22.870
If I...

00:09:22.870 --> 00:09:24.910
If I get run over here...!

00:09:24.910 --> 00:09:26.660
If I let myself die...!

00:09:26.660 --> 00:09:28.870
Something will have to change!

00:09:29.040 --> 00:09:30.910
It'll have to!

00:09:32.080 --> 00:09:33.700
Okarin!

00:09:40.830 --> 00:09:42.290
Mayuri?!

00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:45.540
Mayuri!

00:09:48.830 --> 00:09:52.250
Oka... rin...

00:09:52.250 --> 00:09:57.040
I was finally... finally helpful...

00:09:57.040 --> 00:09:58.700
Mayuri...

00:09:58.700 --> 00:10:00.620
Mayushii...

00:10:01.830 --> 00:10:03.500
...was finally...

00:10:03.500 --> 00:10:06.410
...helpful to you...

00:10:07.950 --> 00:10:12.500
...Oka... rin...

00:10:18.910 --> 00:10:21.620
Hey, Mayuri...

00:10:21.620 --> 00:10:27.040
You can hardly see any stars from here...

00:10:30.200 --> 00:10:33.450
This just isn't fair...

00:10:41.200 --> 00:10:43.290
"We need to talk. -Kurisu"

00:10:54.080 --> 00:10:57.290
I'm gonna run the hack now.

00:10:57.290 --> 00:10:58.910
Okabe?

00:11:01.830 --> 00:11:03.450
Okabe...?

00:11:24.160 --> 00:11:26.580
How long are you gonna stay up here?

00:11:29.160 --> 00:11:31.830
I told you I want to be alone.

00:11:31.830 --> 00:11:32.950
You did.

00:11:32.950 --> 00:11:36.950
But you've been on the roof
for hours, completely silent.

00:11:36.950 --> 00:11:40.580
Of course I'd be worried-- I mean, I wouldn't.

00:11:42.450 --> 00:11:45.870
Tell me. Why did you call off the hack?

00:11:45.870 --> 00:11:48.910
You yourself said we shouldn't.

00:11:48.910 --> 00:11:52.830
You're afraid the fuzz'll
get you, huh? That must be it!

00:11:52.830 --> 00:11:56.040
Call it the awakening of a law-abiding citizen.

00:11:56.040 --> 00:11:57.410
This isn't like you.

00:11:57.410 --> 00:12:00.540
Where did your usual self-righteous attitude go?

00:12:00.540 --> 00:12:05.160
-What kind of a mad scientist--
-This is no time for self-righteousness!

00:12:05.160 --> 00:12:08.910
A mad scientist? Hououin Kyouma?!

00:12:08.910 --> 00:12:12.200
That's all just nonsense! Make-believe!

00:12:12.200 --> 00:12:14.500
Haven't you realized that?!

00:12:16.700 --> 00:12:19.700
I knew from the moment I met you.

00:12:21.250 --> 00:12:24.000
Don't tell me you've
done another time leap?!

00:12:26.000 --> 00:12:28.450
What happened?

00:12:28.450 --> 00:12:33.370
I've helped you so much already.
Don't hold back now.

00:12:33.370 --> 00:12:37.950
Putting our heads together
is what's gotten you this far.

00:12:37.950 --> 00:12:40.910
This far...

00:12:42.040 --> 00:12:45.160
Suzuha, Faris, Rukako...

00:12:45.160 --> 00:12:49.370
Sacrificing all their hopes and
dreams has finally led me here...

00:12:49.370 --> 00:12:53.790
And this is how it ends?

00:12:53.790 --> 00:12:55.910
What do you mean?

00:12:55.910 --> 00:12:57.660
Why...?

00:12:57.660 --> 00:12:59.000
Okabe!

00:13:03.410 --> 00:13:05.330
Listen, Okabe...

00:13:05.330 --> 00:13:09.370
You were crying back there.

00:13:09.370 --> 00:13:11.950
You had Hashida worried too.

00:13:11.950 --> 00:13:16.040
He thought maybe you had
a bad dream or something.

00:13:16.040 --> 00:13:17.660
Tell me.

00:13:19.620 --> 00:13:21.830
I want to help you!

00:13:29.700 --> 00:13:33.830
On July 28th...

00:13:33.830 --> 00:13:37.830
Mayuri and I went to Dr. Nakabachi's conference.

00:13:37.830 --> 00:13:39.620
It was there...

00:13:39.620 --> 00:13:45.910
It was there I found Makise Kurisu
on the ground, stabbed by someone.

00:13:45.910 --> 00:13:49.750
I sent a message to Daru's phone, which
was connected to the Phone Microwave.

00:13:49.750 --> 00:13:52.040
The very first D-mail...

00:13:52.040 --> 00:13:57.620
It's what moved us from the beta
world line to this alpha world line...

00:13:57.620 --> 00:14:01.040
Deleting that message
from SERN's database

00:14:01.040 --> 00:14:03.790
and returning to the beta world line...

00:14:03.790 --> 00:14:06.250
...means returning to that world.

00:14:07.870 --> 00:14:10.330
If we return to the beta world line...

00:14:10.330 --> 00:14:13.250
If we undo that D-mail...

00:14:13.250 --> 00:14:14.750
...you'll die.

00:14:29.540 --> 00:14:31.290
Answer it.

00:14:33.830 --> 00:14:35.450
Answer it...

00:14:37.830 --> 00:14:39.330
Mayuri?

00:14:39.330 --> 00:14:40.370
Yeah.

00:14:40.370 --> 00:14:41.910
What's up?

00:14:41.910 --> 00:14:47.580
Well, Daru-kun said you
were acting strange, so...

00:14:47.580 --> 00:14:50.450
Nothing's wrong. He was mistaken.

00:14:50.450 --> 00:14:52.080
But...

00:14:53.700 --> 00:14:55.410
I'm sorry.

00:14:55.410 --> 00:15:00.620
Mayushii was so caught up in Comima
she didn't pay any attention to you.

00:15:00.620 --> 00:15:05.080
Remember how you used
to tell me all sorts of things?

00:15:05.080 --> 00:15:08.410
Like, let's see, the
Organization has four leaders...

00:15:08.410 --> 00:15:11.200
Geppu, Sudachi, Seiyuu, and Jakko?

00:15:11.200 --> 00:15:14.120
Genbu, Suzaku, Seiryuu, and Byakko.

00:15:14.120 --> 00:15:15.580
Yeah, that's it.

00:15:15.580 --> 00:15:20.910
All that stuff you'd tell me was really neat!

00:15:23.910 --> 00:15:28.620
Anyway, tell me if I ever
feel like a burden to you, okay?

00:15:28.620 --> 00:15:30.250
Well, I'm gonna go for now!

00:15:30.250 --> 00:15:35.000
If there's anything you want
to talk about, just call, okay?

00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:37.120
Mayuri! Wait!

00:15:37.120 --> 00:15:39.330
You should go right now.

00:15:39.330 --> 00:15:43.450
I could guess what she was
saying from the tone of your voice.

00:15:43.450 --> 00:15:46.580
You should go to her right now.

00:15:46.580 --> 00:15:50.410
Sitting here talking about me
won't solve anything right now.

00:15:50.410 --> 00:15:54.500
That's why you were
up here all alone, right?

00:15:54.500 --> 00:15:57.450
So you should go see Mayuri.

00:15:57.450 --> 00:16:02.330
Having you sit here and worry
about me will only hurt my pride.

00:16:02.330 --> 00:16:04.200
I'm going now.

00:16:13.580 --> 00:16:15.200
This is Mayushii!

00:16:15.200 --> 00:16:17.910
I can't come to the phone right now.

00:16:21.620 --> 00:16:22.500
It's me.

00:16:22.500 --> 00:16:26.290
Yeah, some cosplayer
said she left a while ago.

00:16:26.290 --> 00:16:28.120
I see.

00:16:50.120 --> 00:16:52.040
I'm sorry.

00:16:52.040 --> 00:16:55.540
You came to see me for
Obon, didn't you, Granny?

00:16:56.790 --> 00:17:01.700
Actually, I've been having
these scary dreams lately.

00:17:01.700 --> 00:17:06.950
Something terrible always
happens to Mayushii in them.

00:17:06.950 --> 00:17:11.700
Like getting shot by pistols,
getting into car accidents,

00:17:11.700 --> 00:17:14.040
and getting hit by trains...

00:17:14.040 --> 00:17:16.450
It all feels so real

00:17:16.450 --> 00:17:21.160
and scary and painful and sad...

00:17:21.160 --> 00:17:28.120
I try really hard to
shout for help, but I can't...

00:17:28.120 --> 00:17:30.750
I wonder why I have these dreams.

00:17:32.660 --> 00:17:38.660
And then, at the end of them,
Okarin always comes to save me.

00:17:38.660 --> 00:17:45.700
Mayushii tries to thank him,
but he can't hear her.

00:17:47.830 --> 00:17:52.910
He holds Mayushii tight
and looks really sad.

00:17:52.910 --> 00:17:58.250
He never cries, but I can tell
he's fighting hard to hold back.

00:17:58.250 --> 00:18:04.830
So Mayushii tries to say she's
sorry, but he can't hear her...

00:18:04.830 --> 00:18:06.370
And then I wake up.

00:18:09.000 --> 00:18:12.080
Sorry, I'll talk about something nice now!

00:18:12.080 --> 00:18:15.040
We've gained a lot of lab members lately!

00:18:15.040 --> 00:18:21.370
There's Kurisu-chan, Moeka-san,
Ruka-kun, Faris-chan, and Suzu-san.

00:18:21.370 --> 00:18:24.870
I remember when we started
out with only two members!

00:18:24.870 --> 00:18:28.080
Kurisu-chan is really smart

00:18:28.080 --> 00:18:31.290
and talks about tons of
complicated stuff with Okarin.

00:18:31.290 --> 00:18:33.370
It's so nice and lively!

00:18:33.370 --> 00:18:36.950
And Okarin seems happy,
being able to talk so much.

00:18:39.080 --> 00:18:42.910
But, you know, sometimes I think back...

00:18:44.080 --> 00:18:48.290
...to when Mayushii first visited the lab.

00:18:48.750 --> 00:18:52.660
It was snowing, even
though it was early spring...

00:18:53.700 --> 00:18:57.910
I went to the lab after school,
but Okarin wasn't there.

00:18:57.910 --> 00:19:02.790
And then, while I was
tidying up the place, he arrived.

00:19:02.790 --> 00:19:08.000
I said, "Welcome back!"
but he didn't say, "I'm back!"

00:19:08.000 --> 00:19:11.200
Instead, he replied with, "Good work!"

00:19:11.200 --> 00:19:13.870
After that, I spent about
two hours there every day,

00:19:13.870 --> 00:19:16.660
even though we barely ever talked.

00:19:16.660 --> 00:19:23.290
But it wasn't a bad silence.
We were just "there."

00:19:23.290 --> 00:19:28.620
Slowly and gently, time would pass...

00:19:28.620 --> 00:19:32.700
Mayushii almost felt like she was a hostage!

00:19:33.330 --> 00:19:36.120
Did something good happen?

00:19:36.120 --> 00:19:37.200
Mm-hmm!

00:19:37.200 --> 00:19:40.580
Yes... but no!

00:19:40.580 --> 00:19:43.160
Oh? Sounds like you were hallucinating then.

00:19:43.160 --> 00:19:48.080
It could be the work of the Illusion
Conductor, a top Organization leader.

00:19:48.080 --> 00:19:51.700
Really?! Then I better be careful!

00:19:51.700 --> 00:19:54.870
-But I don't think this Illusion Condor--
-Conductor.

00:19:54.870 --> 00:19:56.330
Oh, right.

00:19:56.330 --> 00:20:00.580
I don't think he's actually a bad guy!

00:20:02.290 --> 00:20:08.200
Okarin and I don't talk as much anymore.

00:20:08.200 --> 00:20:13.580
I used to be able to tell what he was
thinking just from seeing his face...

00:20:13.580 --> 00:20:17.330
But lately I can't tell at all.

00:20:17.330 --> 00:20:21.200
All I can tell is that he's in pain...

00:20:21.200 --> 00:20:23.250
That he's suffering...

00:20:23.250 --> 00:20:26.120
He always looks ready to cry...

00:20:26.120 --> 00:20:29.950
And I know it's because of Mayushii...

00:20:32.000 --> 00:20:35.830
I don't mean to be a burden to him, though.

00:20:35.830 --> 00:20:39.540
I'm sorry! I started
talking about sad stuff again!

00:20:39.540 --> 00:20:43.790
I guess maybe Mayushii's feeling lonely.

00:20:45.080 --> 00:20:46.830
Granny...

00:20:46.830 --> 00:20:50.370
I can't stay like this forever, can I?

00:20:52.200 --> 00:20:54.040
You can.

00:20:57.290 --> 00:20:59.160
O--

00:20:59.160 --> 00:21:00.790
Okarin!

00:21:04.580 --> 00:21:06.500
How did you know where to find me?

00:21:06.500 --> 00:21:11.160
I always know where my hostage is.

00:21:11.160 --> 00:21:13.910
You will never escape my clutches.

00:21:13.910 --> 00:21:15.540
Never.

00:21:16.410 --> 00:21:19.120
Don't push yourself too hard, okay?

00:21:22.120 --> 00:21:27.160
Hououin Kyouma is not so weak
that he needs you to worry about him.

00:21:28.660 --> 00:21:30.910
I'll tell you everything...

00:21:30.910 --> 00:21:32.790
...when the time comes.

00:21:33.660 --> 00:21:34.950
Okay.

00:21:34.950 --> 00:21:37.790
-Let's go.
-Oh, but first--!

00:21:37.790 --> 00:21:39.330
I know.

00:21:39.330 --> 00:21:42.160
You want to get another Oopa, don't you?

00:22:20.700 --> 00:22:23.750
With my vision restricted,

00:22:23.750 --> 00:22:29.620
there's no escape

00:22:29.620 --> 00:22:32.580
from the merciless control

00:22:32.580 --> 00:22:37.410
of the twelve

00:22:37.410 --> 00:22:41.410
Wishing for

00:22:41.410 --> 00:22:46.290
a tomorrow of repose,

00:22:46.290 --> 00:22:50.370
I embark for the horizon

00:22:50.370 --> 00:22:54.870
of the sacred phenomenon in my hand

00:22:54.870 --> 00:22:59.120
Trapped by the covenant

00:22:59.120 --> 00:23:03.500
and shown the outline of false evidence

00:23:03.500 --> 00:23:07.660
the heaven and earth

00:23:07.660 --> 00:23:12.620
of life lets time blindly flow by

00:23:12.620 --> 00:23:17.950
Flutter, butterfly, oh, miraculous butterfly!

00:23:17.950 --> 00:23:21.500
I give myself to you

00:23:21.500 --> 00:23:25.950
Oh, butterfly of tears, dazzling butterfly!

00:23:25.950 --> 00:23:28.750
It's all...

00:23:28.750 --> 00:23:33.660
...about to be rewritten now

